.TH ABRAFLEXI-MATCH-RECEIVED-PAYMENT 1 "July 17, 2026" "abraflexi-matcher" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
abraflexi-match-received-payment \- Match one specific received payment to an issued invoice in AbraFlexi
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B abraflexi-match-received-payment
.RB [ \-o
.IR output_file ]
.RB [ \-\-output= "" output_file "" ]
.RB [ \-e
.IR env_file ]
.RB [ \-\-environment= "" env_file "" ]
.RI [ DOCUMENTID ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B abraflexi-match-received-payment
looks up one incoming bank payment, identified by
.IR DOCUMENTID
(AbraFlexi banka document code or numeric ID), and attempts to match it to
an issued invoice. Intended for on-demand/webhook-driven matching of a
single payment as soon as it arrives, rather than a scheduled batch pass.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output = \fIFILE\fR
Write the JSON report to
.I FILE
instead of the location given by
.B RESULT_FILE
(or stdout).
.TP
.BR \-e ", " \-\-environment = \fIFILE\fR
Load configuration from
.I FILE
instead of
.B ../.env
.TP
.RI [ DOCUMENTID ]
AbraFlexi banka document code or numeric ID to match. Overrides the
.B DOCUMENTID
environment variable when given.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B DOCUMENTID
AbraFlexi banka document code or numeric ID to match, used when no
command-line argument is given.
.TP
.B RESULT_FILE
Path to the output JSON report file (default: payment_match_report.json)
.TP
.B MATCHER_LOCALIZE
Locale for log/report messages: en_US (default), cs_CZ, or sk_SK.
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_URL
AbraFlexi server URL
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_LOGIN
AbraFlexi login username
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_PASSWORD
AbraFlexi password
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_COMPANY
AbraFlexi company code
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success \- payment matched to an invoice.
.TP
.B 1
Payment record not found in AbraFlexi (DOCUMENTID missing or invalid).
.TP
.B 2
Payment found but could not be matched to an invoice.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I payment_match_report.json
Default output file containing the matching result in JSON format compliant with the multiflexi report schema.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR abraflexi-match-bank (1),
.BR abraflexi-matcher-in (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Written by Vitex Software.
